SRC="../graphics/chipheader.gif" usemap="#header" BORDER=0 WIDTH="476"
HEIGHT="58"></A><BR><IMG SRC="../graphics/hangerexplorations.gif"
WIDTH="476" HEIGHT="27"><P>EAGLE NEBULA is a stellar nursery.
Ultraviolet radiation from young stars eats away at dark gas in the
nebula, creating the bizarre pillar formations seen here. Within the
thick knots at the top of the pillars are dense globules where stars
are beingborn. Infant stars are usually surrounded by thick disks of
gas and dust--the likely building blocks of planets.<P><IMG
SRC="IMG/052796explorationsbox4.gif" WIDTH="467" HEIGHT="462"
BORDER="0">Image courtesy NASA/<A
HREF="http://www.stsci.edu/pubinfo/PR/95/44.html">Space Telescope
