<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<table border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td><img src="/gifs/acri.gif" alt="ACRI Logo" width="102"
        height="225"> </td>
        <td align="center" colspan="2"><font size="7"><b>ACRI</b>
        Society </font><p><font size="4">MECANIQUE DES FLUIDES <br>
        OBSERVATION DE LA TERRE <br>
        SCIENCES DE L'ENVIRONNEMENT </font></p>
        <p><a href="/French/Societe/societe.html"><font size="4"><img
        src="/gifs/frenchflag.gif" alt="French Flag"
        align="middle" width="40" height="30"> Cliquer ici pour
        obtenir la version franaise </font></a></p>
        </td>
    </tr>
<!--an empty line-->    <tr>
        <td colspan="3"><img src="/gifs/france.gif"
        alt="France Map" align="top" width="491" height="335"> </td>
    </tr>
<!--The company-->    <tr>
        <td>ACRI S.A. </td>
        <td><img src="/gifs/acri_little_house.gif" align="middle"
        width="235" height="75"> </td>
        <td><a href="profile.html">Society Profil</a> </td>
    </tr>
<!--an empty line-->    <tr>
        <td colspan="3"><font size="4">ACRI is a high technology
        company which was created in Sophia-Antipolis in 1989.
        Its main activities are in Fluid Dynamics and in the
        remote sensing applications of the Earth and its
        environment.<br>
        ACRI is a recognized supplier of Scientific Research ans
        Development services. ACRI performs studies ans produces
        end to end performance simulators for space-borne Earth
        remote sensing systems. </font><ul>
            <li><font size="4">User requirements analysis </font></li>
            <li><font size="4">System and mission analysis </font></li>
            <li><font size="4">Simulation of acquisition data
                chain performance </font></li>
            <li><font size="4">Image data products definition </font></li>
            <li><font size="4">Geophysical algorithms
                development, in tight co-operation with
                scientific laboratories </font></li>
        </ul>
        <p><font size="4">In the area of Fluid Dynamics, ACRI
        develops software and provides engineering and scientific
        support </font></p>
        <ul>
            <li><font size="4">Environmental impact studies </font></li>
            <li><font size="4">Coastal engineering </font></li>
            <li><font size="4">Hydrodynamics and Oceanography </font></li>
            <li><font size="4">Industrial processes </font></li>
            <li><font size="4">Environmental transport processes </font></li>
        </ul>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>

<p align="center"><!--Description--> </p>
