<HEAD>
<TITLE> TIDAL Example </TITLE>
<!-- Created by: David Lajoie, 08-Feb-1996 -->
</HEAD>

<BODY  BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">
<CENTER>

<H1> Seiche in PORT TUDY <P>
(GROIX ISLAND)
</H1>

<HR>
</CENTER>

<big>
The water surface of "PORT TUDY" (the Groix Island harbour situated few kilometers south of Britain in France) is sometimes subject to oscillations induced by a long period oscillation water wave, also called a seiche. The seiche is set between the continent and the island and has a period of five minutes. The wave amplitude may be greater than one meter, so that strong currents may be generated inside the harbour.<P>

Modulus of velocity (considered constant on the depth) inside the harbour are reported on the picture below. It is possible to follow the corresponding animation for a complete period of the seiche.
<p>

<center>
<a href ="/mpeg/groix.mpg"><img alt="groix picture" src="gifs/groix1.gif"><p>
Click here or on the picture if you want to see the animation</a> (316K)<p></a>
You need to have a mpeg viewer on your system to run the animation<p>
</center>
</big>

<P>
<IMG align=top src="/gifs/bar_marbre_noir2.gif">

