<HTML>

  <HEAD>
    <TITLE> TIDAL </TITLE>
    <!-- Created by: Gilbert BARROT, 25-Jan-1996 -->
    <!-- Changed by: Gilbert BARROT, 25-Jan-1996 -->
    <!-- Changed by: ,  7-Mar-1996 -->
  </HEAD>

  <BODY  BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">

      <CENTER>
      <H1> 
	TIDAL<P>
	A model for dynamic analysis of water elevation and current patterns in large, shallow water bodies<P>
      </H1>
      </CENTER>

      <FONT SIZE="+2">
	A demonstration is available <A HREF="/English/Products/download.html">here</A>.
      </FONT>

      <HR>
      <CENTER>
	<IMG ALIGN=TOP ALT="TIDAL Main example" SRC="gifs/tidal.gif"><P>
      </CENTER>

      <HR>

      <BIG>
	The software TIDAL is a tool for the simulation of coastal hydrodynamics
	and water quality for large areas as bays, estuaries, lakes and nearshore 
	area.<P>

	It allows to take into account several physical phenomena such as
	currents, tides, winds, gravity and Coriolis forces, friction bottom,
	heat transfer and chemical reactions. Flooding and draining may also
	be considered. The computation is made for stationnary or
	time-dependent phenomena for any geometry of the site (including
	islands). Modelisation of inlets and/or outlets is performed when
	introducing one or several fluid and/or pollutant sources.<P>

	The output of the model are, for any points of the site, the intensity
	and direction of the current velocity, the concentration of one or
	several chemical species, the local water level and the
	temperature.<P>

	The basic equations discretisation is obtained by the use of a finite
	volume method and an ADI scheme. Depending on the study, it is
	possible to perform the resolution of the final matrical problem by
	different methods : Gauss, Cholesky, conjugated gradient, modified
	ADI.<P>

	The user interface is through the conversational FREEFORM language
	which provides for simple English-like command syntax. The result can
	be graphically displayed by the acrPLOT post-processor, which can
	generate charts for flow vectors, contours, isovalue rasters, grids,
	3D surface plots and X-Y plots at any cross section.<P><P> </BIG>

	<BIG> Keywords :
      <UL>
	<LI> Bathymetry & coastal boundary
	<LI> Current & water level
	<LI> Temperature & salinity
	<LI> Water quality parameters
	<LI> Tides, wind, bottom friction
	<LI> Coriolis & body forces
	<LI> Chemical & biological reactions
	<LI> Flood lands
	<LI> Freshwater, heat & mass sources
      </UL>
    </BIG>

      <HR>

      <CENTER>
      <H2> 
	Some examples<P>
      </H2>
      </CENTER>

      <DL>
	<DT><DD><A HREF="acheres.html"><H3>Acheres</H3></A>
	<DT><DD><A HREF="caen.html"><H3>Caen</H3></A>
	<DT><DD><A HREF="groix.html"><H3>Groix</H3></A>
	<DT><DD><A HREF="nacre.html"><H3>Evolution of an oil slick</H3></A>
	<DT><DD><A HREF="gifs/tidal.dat"><H3>Dataset example</H3></A>
      </DL>

      <P>
<IMG align=top src="/gifs/bar_marbre_noir2.gif">

