<HTML>

<HEAD>
<TITLE> PORFLOW Examples </TITLE>
<!-- Created by: Jennifer Haase, 20-Mar-1996 -->
</HEAD>

<BODY  BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">

<HR>

<CENTER>
<H1> 
PORFLOW Examples<P>
</H1>
<H2>
Transient Infiltration of Water in Heterogeneous Soil
</H2>
</CENTER>
<HR>


PORFLOW has the capability to calculate fluid transport in 3-D heterogeneous
media and the flexibility to use arbitrary user-specified
soil moisture characteristics.
<P>
 <IMG ALIGN=TOP ALT="titre" SRC="gifs/time20.gif"><P>
<H3>
<CENTER>
Moisture Content in Heterogeneous Soil after 20 Days <P>
</CENTER>
</H3>
<CENTER>
<a href="/mpeg/porflow.mpg">Click here if you would like to see the animation</a>(200K)<BR>
(You must have a mpeg viewer on your system.)
</CENTER>
<P>
Here we present an example of a 2-D calculation of transient moisture
content in heterogeneous soil. 
The 800 by 650 cm test area comprises three layers of soil which vary in material and hydrological
properties. A small zone of high conductivity soil is contained within the lowermost
soil near the left boundary. Uniform infiltration of water at 2 cm/day occurs at the top left boundary.
<P>
The effect of the embedded high-conductivity zone of soil is clearly seen in the manner 
in which the moisture contours deflect towards this zone.

<HR>

<P>
<IMG align=top src="/gifs/bar_marbre_noir2.gif">

<TABLE BORDER=3 >
<tr><td><a href="/English/Studies/studies.html"> <BIG><strong>Studies</BIG></strong></td>
<td><a href="/English/Products/products.html"> <BIG><strong>Products</strong></BIG>
<td><a href="/index.html"><img align = middle border=0  src="/gifs/backacri.gif" ALT="ACRI"></a></td>
<td><A HREF="mailto:www@acri.fr"><IMG border=0 ALIGN=TOP SRC="/gifs/Email2.gif" ALT="ACRI Email"></A></td>
</TABLE>



