<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Coastal Zone Data</TITLE>
<!-- Created by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 11-Jan-1995 -->
<!-- Changed by: Jean-Michel Augusto, 30-Jan-1996 -->


</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/gifs/fond.jpg">

<IMG ALIGN=TOP SRC="/gifs/ceolineup.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/backceo.gif" ALT="Coastal page"></A>
<A HREF="cz_help.html"><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/help.gif"></A>
<BR>
<IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/ceolinedown.gif">

<H1>Real-time Measurement</H1>

<DL>
<DT><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="/gifs/note.gif">
<DD><I>
The following data are made available with the help and agreement of
<STRONG>CLS ARGOS</STRONG> and the owners of the data:
<STRONG>'PUERTOS DEL ESTADO' of the Spanish Ministry of Public Works</STRONG>
for Bilbao buoy and <STRONG> METEO FRANCE </STRONG> for Marisonde buoy.
</I>
</DL>

<H3>
This server allows to get real-time measurement (updated each 12 hours)
comming from drifting buoys. These information are transmited using the Argos system
and the CLS Argos society support.
<P>
We have planed to make four buoys data available in this demonstration step.
You can also access to data <A HREF="cz_map.html"> by clicking on a map </A>.

Today, only the two first are updated on real-time
<DL>
<DL>
<DT><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/whiteball.gif">SEATEX buoy in front of Bilbao
<DL>
<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">
<A HREF="cz_jrc.html">
<b>RAW FORMAT</b> </A>

<DT> <IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif">
<A HREF="http://me-www.jrc.it/acri/data/test.html">
<b>GRAPHIC FORMAT </b> with display computed at ISPRA. </A>
</DL>


<DT><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="/gifs/yellowball.gif"><A HREF="/cgi-bin/make_marisonde_14419">MARISONDE drifting buoy</A> Oceano-meteorological data (ID 14419)

<DT><IMG ALIGN=BTOOM SRC="/gifs/redball.gif"><A HREF="/cgi-bin/make_marisonde_14421">MARISONDE drifting buoy</A> Oceano-meteorological data (ID 14421)
</DL>
</DL>


<DL>

This service is still at prototype level. So, don't hesitate to give
us your <A HREF="cz_interests.html">feedback</A> about this
service and the available data.



<HR WIDTH="75%" NOSHADE>
      
